<subSubSection id="5897F4F83C024B2DFF47BA7AFC8242D0" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="1032A7733C024B2DFF47BA7AFC8242D0" blockId="9.[151,1437,1367,2042]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C024B2DFF47BA7AFE3641D7" bold="true" box="[199,453,1403,1429]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Diagnosis (emended).</emphasis>
Prostomium wider than long. Two antennae; two palps similar in size/shape to antennae. No median antenna or nuchal papilla. Nuchal organs unknown. Eyes absent. Smooth proboscis, papillae at distal end. Segment 1 fused or not (dorsally) to prostomium. Segment 1 distinct ventrally. Elongated dorsal cirri (EDC) (= tentacular cirri) on segments 1, 2; EDC on segment 3. No ventral cirri on segment 1. Ventral cirri on segment 2 elongated or like following segments. Parapodia uniramous, notopodial chaetae absent. Neuropodium with central fascicle containing compound chaetae; one simple emergent acicula. Compound chaetal shaft cylindrical; pointed blade extended from falcate joint. Rostrum of chaetal shaft asymmetrical/hooked. Presence of segmental bands of cilia. Pygidial cirri robust ellipsoid lobes. Living animals are red.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5897F4F83C024B2DFF47B99DFB2043B8" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="1032A7733C024B2DFF47B99DFB2043B8" blockId="9.[151,1437,1367,2042]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C024B2DFF47B99DFEC842F4" bold="true" box="[199,315,1692,1718]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Remarks.</emphasis>
Based on this study, 
<taxonomicName id="D78DDCF03C024B2DFDA3B99DFD0042F4" authorityName="Blake" authorityYear="1985" box="[547,755,1692,1718]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C024B2DFDA3B99DFD0042F4" box="[547,755,1692,1718]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Galapagomystides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
now includes five species; 
<taxonomicName id="D78DDCF03C024B2DFBA2B99DFB6842F7" authorityName=", Blake" authorityYear="1985" box="[1058,1179,1692,1718]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="aristata">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C024B2DFBA2B99DFB6842F7" box="[1058,1179,1692,1718]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">G. aristata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D78DDCF03C024B2DFB28B99DFAA642F4" authority="Pearson &amp; Rouse, 2022" authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" box="[1192,1365,1692,1718]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bobpearsoni" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C024B2DFB28B99DFAA642F4" box="[1192,1365,1692,1718]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">G. bobpearsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="39CAC61A3C024B2DFADAB99DFA6442F4" box="[1370,1431,1692,1718]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D78DDCF03C024B2DFF17B9C1FEE24298" authority="Pearson &amp; Rouse, 2022" authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,273,1728,1754]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="kathyae" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C024B2DFF17B9C1FEE24298" box="[151,273,1728,1754]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">G. kathyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="39CAC61A3C024B2DFE99B9C1FEA44298" box="[281,343,1728,1754]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D78DDCF03C024B2DFEE4B9C1FE2D4298" authority="Pearson &amp; Rouse, 2022" authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" box="[356,478,1728,1754]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="patricki" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C024B2DFEE4B9C1FE2D4298" box="[356,478,1728,1754]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">G. patricki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="39CAC61A3C024B2DFE66B9C1FDD74298" box="[486,548,1728,1754]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="D78DDCF03C024B2DFDE2B9C1FD2F429B" authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Blake and Hilbig" baseAuthorityYear="1990" box="[610,732,1728,1754]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="verenae" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C024B2DFDE2B9C1FD2F429B" box="[610,732,1728,1754]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">G. verenae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="39CAC61A3C024B2DFD64B9C1FCB54298" box="[740,838,1728,1754]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" rank="species">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<bibRefCitation id="741CDA823C024B2DFCCDB9C1FC074298" author="Blake, J. A." box="[845,1012,1727,1754]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" pagination="67 - 101" refId="ref14106" refString="Blake, J. A. (1985) Polychaeta from the vicinity of deep-sea geothermal vents in the eastern pacific. I. Euphrosinidae, Phyllodocidae, Hesionidae, Nereididae, Glyceridae, Dorvilleidae, Orbiniidae, and Maldanidae. Bulletin of the Biological Society of Washington, 6, 67 - 101." type="journal article" year="1985">Blake’s (1985)</bibRefCitation>
original 
<taxonomicName id="D78DDCF03C024B2DFBDAB9C1FAD94298" authorityName="Blake" authorityYear="1985" box="[1114,1322,1728,1754]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C024B2DFBDAB9C1FAD94298" box="[1114,1322,1728,1754]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Galapagomystides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
diagnosis stated that the genus has segment 1 fused dorsally to the prostomium, and no dorsal cirri on segment 3. We amend the 
<taxonomicName id="D78DDCF03C024B2DFF40B809FE634360" authorityName="Blake" authorityYear="1985" box="[192,400,1800,1826]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C024B2DFF40B809FE634360" box="[192,400,1800,1826]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Galapagomystides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
diagnosis to allow for the variation shown in other members of the genus. For instance, some taxa do not have segment 1 fused to the prostomium and may have dorsal elongated cirri on segment 
<quantity id="D7750A963C024B2DFB75B82DFAEC4304" box="[1269,1311,1836,1862]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" unit="in" value="3.0">3 in</quantity>
addition to segments 1 and 2 (
<tableCitation id="5D0F92C83C024B2DFEE3B851FE494328" box="[355,442,1872,1898]" captionStart="TABLE 4" captionStartId="10.[151,239,151,175]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="TABLE 4. Features of Galapagomystides species. (P) = present. (A) = absent." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/44F2F7FB3C014B2EFF17BF96FC2844ED" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" tableUuid="44F2F7FB3C014B2EFF17BF96FC2844ED">Table 4</tableCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="741CDA823C024B2DFE4DB851FD8B4328" author="Pleijel, F." box="[461,632,1872,1898]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" pagination="225 - 261" refId="ref17152" refString="Pleijel, F. (1991) Phylogeny and classification of the Phyllodocidae (Polychaeta). Zoologica Scripta, 20, 225 - 261. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.1991. tb 00289. x" type="journal article" year="1991">Pleijel’s (1991)</bibRefCitation>
diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName id="D78DDCF03C024B2DFC8BB851FC284328" authorityName="Blake" authorityYear="1985" box="[779,987,1872,1898]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C024B2DFC8BB851FC284328" box="[779,987,1872,1898]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Galapagomystides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
accepted 
<bibRefCitation id="741CDA823C024B2DFBC9B851FB1D4328" author="Blake, J. A." box="[1097,1262,1871,1898]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" pagination="67 - 101" refId="ref14106" refString="Blake, J. A. (1985) Polychaeta from the vicinity of deep-sea geothermal vents in the eastern pacific. I. Euphrosinidae, Phyllodocidae, Hesionidae, Nereididae, Glyceridae, Dorvilleidae, Orbiniidae, and Maldanidae. Bulletin of the Biological Society of Washington, 6, 67 - 101." type="journal article" year="1985">Blake’s (1985)</bibRefCitation>
diagnosis, with the addition of nuchal organs present as dorso-lateral ciliated pits between the prostomium and segment 1. 
<bibRefCitation id="741CDA823C024B2DFAD5B875FF1143F0" author="Pleijel, F." pageId="9" pageNumber="460" pagination="225 - 261" refId="ref17152" refString="Pleijel, F. (1991) Phylogeny and classification of the Phyllodocidae (Polychaeta). Zoologica Scripta, 20, 225 - 261. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.1991. tb 00289. x" type="journal article" year="1991">Pleijel (1991)</bibRefCitation>
also questioned the presence of segmental ciliated bands though their presence is confirmed here. All species within 
<taxonomicName id="D78DDCF03C024B2DFF65B8BDFE464394" authorityName="Blake" authorityYear="1985" box="[229,437,1980,2006]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C024B2DFF65B8BDFE464394" box="[229,437,1980,2006]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Galapagomystides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
